column36: Overall, it is easy and intuitive to use the system. The biggest problem was figuring out the home menu with the 3 graph types. It was not obvious to swipe to reveal the home menu, or to swipe the name of the graph to discard it from the view. I eventually figured these interactions out.

column36: Didnt discover the swipe functionality on the titles until later. Some soft of signifier would be useful. It makes you discover stuff on your own - which I liked and disliked. Liked -because it kept the space clean and the interface looks pleasant. But as I mentioned before signifiers in some places would enable shorter learning time.
column37: Also, really liked the swipe out functionality to filter out certain things. Didnt really use the line chart visualization at all. Used the bar chart for pretty much all I answered. Dont understand what the grey boxes are in the horizontal bar charts. Otherwise looks like a pretty useful system. Interactivity is great.
